post_text:
Federal Programs Meetings Announced - Two of Wayne Public Schools Federal Programs are having meetings. First, the Indian Education Parent Committee is having its fall meeting on Thursday, September 10 at 5:30 pm. It is for all parents of students with tribal citizenship. It will be held in the High School Library or you may attend by a Google Meet link. Email Michelle Matthews at micmatthews@wayne.k12.ok.us for the link if you want to attend that way.

The Title I/REAP Flex Teacher/Parent Committee meeting will be held Thursday, September 17 at 3:30 pm, also in the High School library. This is for parents of all students of Wayne Schools. We will discuss budgets for the 2020-2021 school year.

Please wear a mask to the meetings and prepare to socially distance. An agenda will be available by email for anyone attending. http://edl.io/n1292003

post_text: The kindergarten class is learning about CHARACTERS this week! They made one of their favorite Toy Story Characters today....Forky!!! He was just as ornery today as he was in the movie. He jumped right off their desks and tried to throw himself away in our trash can! The kids went into panic mode and looked everywhere for their missing toy!! I sure hope he stays put when he gets home today! He is kinda sneeky! P.S. Yes the trash can was cLeAn!!!ぉ

Why 2020 Census Matters for Schools - The 2020 Census count impacts the federal funds that communities receive each year for programs and services that are critical for schools, students, and younger children, such as:

-Special education, Head Start, after-school programs, and classroom technology.
-Food assistance, including free and reduced-price school lunches.
-Maternal and child health programs.

Be counted today. http://edl.io/n1281920

Important Information for Graduation
Saturday Night at 8 pm
D.S. "Zack" Powell Stadium

~Masks are highly suggested for Seniors and graduation guests.
~We will have some masks available for Seniors if needed.
~Social Distancing is strongly encouraged.
~Parking in the football field area is prohibited.
~Blankets only on the field at this time due to the amount of rain we have received.
~Graduation guests may sit on the visitor bleachers or the field.
~Seniors will be seated on the home bleachers.
~Graduation will be live-streamed here on Facebook for those unable to attend.

post_text:
Don't forget to fill out this form for Online Enrollment before July 27. In-person enrollment will be very limited.

If you have already pre-enrolled for Pre-K it is not necessary to fill this out.
shared_text:
DOCS.GOOGLE.COM
Online Enrollment Account Setup 2020-2021

Wayne Public Schools
July 20 at 5:46 PM 路

Wayne Public Schools will be doing ONLINE Enrollment for the 2020-2021 school year for students Kindergarten through 12th grade. Enrollment will open July 27 to August 6, 2020.

If you are an existing student guardian, please fill out the Google form BEFORE JULY 27 so your account can be set up correctly for online enrollment. If you are a new student guardian, please fill out the form BEFORE JULY 27 and you will be given the information to begin enrollment. We will create you an account and email you the username and password.

After we get your account set up, you will need to upload items into the system. PDFs are the preferred attachment, but you can attach cell phone pictures if needed.

You will need a birth certificate, shot record (or fill out the OSIIS Authorization), utility bill, and copies of necessary court documents. All items are listed online.

Limited in-person appointments for the week of August 3-6 can be made by emailing wpshelpdesk@wayne.k12.ok.us

You will need a birth certificate, shot record (or fill out the OSIIS Authorization), utility bill, and copies of necessary court documents. All items are listed online.

Limited in-person appointments for the week of August 3-6 can be made by emailing wpshelpdesk@wayne.k12.ok.us

A few notes about the parade:

We will be going throughout the town so it would be nice if the spectators would spread out in different places. Try not to all gather in one spot.

We are still not allowed to gather in large groups at the school so you will have to maintain safe distance from each other. If you have other places in town you could go that would be wonderful. If you are taking pictures of family please do that at home before the seniors line up.

post_text:
Three WHS Seniors Named Oklahoma Academic Scholars in 2020 - Sean Connor Crawford, Katlyn Powell, and James Spencer have all been named Oklahoma Academic Scholars by the State of Oklahoma Department of Education.

Graduating seniors who meet all of the requirements listed below shall be recognized by the local school district and the State Board of Education as an Oklahoma Academic Scholar:

*Accumulate over Grades 9, 10, 11, and the first semester of Grade 12, a minimum grade point average of 3.7 on a 4.0 scale or be in the top 10% of their graduating class.
*Complete (or will complete) the curricular requirements for a standard diploma.
*Achieve a 27 composite score on the ACT or 1220 combined reading and mathematics score on the SAT.

Congratulations to our OAS graduates!

Wayne Public Schools is proud of the Senior Class of 2020! We will be posting one Senior a day as a SENIOR SALUTE! Todays Senior is:

James Dean Spencer

James is one of our Valedictorians and a Top Ten of the Class of 2020. He is the son of Jim and Raquel Spencer. James played football and basketball and was named Captain in each of those sports his senior year. He was also Defensive Back of the Year in football. He was a member of the Student Council, National Honor Society, FCA, and was listed on the Superintendent's Honor Roll every semester. His senior year he was named Class Favorite, Mr. WHS, and was a recipient of the FCA All-State award. James will attend Southeastern Oklahoma State University in the Honors Program. His career path is still undecided.

Wayne Schools Will Be Closed the Remainder of the Year - The Oklahoma State School Board has ruled that all schools in the state will be closed for the remainder of the year. All extracurricular activities and school events are hereby suspended. We will be providing distance learning opportunities for all students to continue to learn and the internet or devices are not going to be required.
We are looking at options for Graduation 2020 that will maintain the guidelines provided by the state, but still honor our seniors.
Please check our website, app, or social media for more information coming out in the next few weeks. Any questions please email wayneschools@wayne.k12.ok.us. http://edl.io/n1197299

post_text: Applications are available online at Chickasaw.net/SummerEBT
shared_text:
The Chickasaw Nation
February 21 at 3:33 PM 路

Chickasaw Nation Nutrition Services is accepting applications for the Summer EBT for Children program. To qualify, your child must be enrolled in a participating school district and receive free or reduced meals at school. Qualifying families will receive approximately $30 of food per child, per month during the three summer months.

Benefits are received on an EBT card that allows families to conveniently purchase healthy food for the summer. This federally funded program is open to both Native and non-Native families.

To view a list of participating school districts and apply, visit Chickasaw.net/SummerEBT or call (844) 256-3467.

post_text: After learning about precipitation and evaporation, Mrs Mead's 3rd grade class conducted a science experiment that would make the Oopa-loompa's on Charlie and the Chocolate Factory... jealous?? We are now patiently awaiting the water to evaporate from our super-sugar-saturated-solution. Each day the students will get to check their jar and watch the sugar crystals grow. The process should take about 10 days and then the students will enjoy them with their classmates and be sent home with sugar running through their veins. :)

The food donation boxes in the middle school are empty! Our goal in the middle school is to collect 500 dry good items for the Thanksgiving Food Drive.
If we meet our goal Principal Brandon Sharp will take a pie to the face!!!
So please help us reach our goal and help local families receive a wonderful food blessing this Thanksgiving.

post_text:
Wayne Middle School had its annual Red Ribbon Week poster and essay contest. Seventh grade student Beatriz Perez took the 1st prize with her essay, while Addison Keeler garnered 2nd, and Myleigh Caballero 3rd. Receiving honorable mentions were Xavier Guerrero, Madilyn Sharp, Theresa Howard, Zoe Overley, Grace Peterson, Alyia Manus, and Madison Deck.
The 1st place poster was created in a joint effort by Karlie Taylor and Kira Dutton. Xavier Guerrero placed 2nd, and Ricky Cooper 3rd. Honorable Mention was given to Dakota Schuman, Ashlyn Kirkland, Karsen Adams, Kamille McGee, Indiana Humbarger, Myleigh Caballero,and Alyia Manus.

Also included are the costume contest winners: 1st place in Scariest- Kiley Pounds
1st Place in Funniest-Aurelio Lopez
1st Place in Best Overall-Cash Sharp 1st place group was the VSCO girls.

Special thanks to Smileys for pizza and drink certificates for the 1st place winners!

post_text: Water levels seem to be to normal! Toilets are flushing so its back to school. Bottled water will still be used for hand washing and drinking. We will communicate with you if something changes.

post_text: Due to town water pressure being low, Wayne Schools has only a few toilets in operation. We have a plan to use those and have portapotties brought in. However, if you decide to keep your child home today or pick them up they will not be counted absent. Thank you for understanding

post_text:
Wayne Schools Will Be in Session on Wednesday, August 14th

The safety of our students is our top priority. Each school is taking safety precautions to protect its students from the water issue in Wayne.

We will have a ready supply of hand sanitizer and bottled water on hand for our students to use. We will be following the situation in Wayne carefully and will communicate further as we find out more information. Any questions or concerns please call the school directly.

post_text:
ALL SCHOOL ENROLLMENT
AUGUST 5TH AND 6TH
8AM -3PM IN CAFETERIA

ALL RETURNING STUDENTS must bring in an up to date immunization record and proof of address.
ALL NEW STUDENTS must bring in State Issued Birth Certificate, Social Security Card, Immunization Record, Proof of Address, and CDIB cards if applicable.

Preferred proof of address is an utility bill or lease agreement.

Please ensure your Pre-K, Kindergarten, and 7th grade children are current on immunizations. See the Oklahoma Immunization Schedule below.

If your child owes lunch or library fees from the previous school year, please settle those balances at enrollment.
